ction during the first month of life for four representative subjects. The solid line represents the cubic smoothing spline fit to the estimated cumulative Hb produced (+). The other solid line represents the dynamic changes in body weight-scaled Hb production rate during the first month of life", "Influence of GA on the postnatal Hb production. The individual data points represent the estimated body weight-scaled postnatal Hb production rate over the first week of life vs. the GA for the 79 VLBW and ELBW anemic preterm study infants"]}
